<p>
  I cobbled together this little routine to use the Indy Component (v10) to
  decode some base-64 encoded information. I chose the <var>TBytes</var>
  return type because base-64 encoding can be used for any sequence of
  &quot;octets&quot;. I thought it better to not return a string since that
  implies text was encoded. We can easily return a string from the byte array.
</p>

<p>
  As well as <var>TBytes</var> I'm using the relatively new
  <var>TBytesStream</var> stream class, so you will need to make some changes
  if using older Delphis.
</p>

